comments.body:
If the `findsWidgets` matcher (i.e. `_FindsWidgetMatcher`) were _also_ callable, then the same identifier could be reused instead of adding `N` in the name (which looks kinda weird there). Examples:

``` dart
expect(find.text('Save'), findsWidgets);
expect(find.text('Save'), findsWidgets(2));
```

For this to work the `_FindsWidgetMatcher` interface would have to be along the following lines:

``` dart
const CallableMatcher findsWidgets = const _FindsWidgetMatcher(1, null);

// This is needed so that callability type checks/auto-completes.
abstract class CallableMatcher {
  Matcher call(int n);
}

class _FindsWidgetMatcher extends Matcher implements CallableMatcher {
  Matcher call(int n) {
    return new _FindsWidgetMatcher(n, n);
  }
}
```

